  <summary>2/26/1998--Introduced.
Small Business Pension Start-Up Credit Act of 1998 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to permit a three-year business credit of 50 percent of small employer pension plan start-up costs, with a limit of $1000 for the first year and $500 for each of the second and third years.</summary>
